stylometry: It imitates real life solutions while incorporating uncertainty in the input variables getting random and various values.  This shows an entire distribution of results having different values for uncertain quantitys, not just a single result.  You would want to use this in a business situation because it will answer "what if" questions. There may be uncertainties in things such as demand but this will show you the solutions for all sorts of damands, then, from there you can make a business decision.
